  "transcript": [
    {
      "id": "line-000",
      "start": 0.0,
      "end": 5.24,
      "text": "This is a Libra-Vox recording. All Libra-Vox recordings are in the public domain.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-001",
      "start": 6.24,
      "end": 11.8,
      "text": "For more information or to volunteer, please visit LibraVox.org.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-002",
      "start": 13.12,
      "end": 16.86,
      "text": "Asop's fables, the goods and the ills.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 17.72,
      "end": 24.28,
      "text": "There was a time in the youth of the world when goods and ills entered equally into the concerns of men,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 24.28,
      "end": 28.14,
      "text": "so that the goods did not prevail to make them altogether blessed,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.76,
      "end": 30.96,
      "text": "knew the ills to make them wholly miserable.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 32.2,
      "end": 39.18,
      "text": "But owing to the foolishness of mankind, the ills multiplied greatly in number and increased in strength,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 39.88,
      "end": 44.38,
      "text": "until it seemed as though they would deprive the goods of all share in human affairs,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 45.22,
      "end": 46.6,
      "text": "and banish them from the earth.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-009",
      "start": 47.6,
      "end": 50.5,
      "text": "The latter, therefore, be took themselves to heaven,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-010",
      "start": 51.06,
      "end": 53.86,
      "text": "and complained to Jupiter of the treatment they had received.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-011",
      "start": 54.76,
      "end": 58.38,
      "text": "At the same time, praying to him to grant them protection from the ills,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-012",
      "start": 58.8,
      "end": 62.1,
      "text": "and to advise them concerning the manner of their intercourse with men.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-013",
      "start": 62.86,
      "end": 66.76,
      "text": "Jupiter granted their request for protection, and decreed that for the future,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-014",
      "start": 67.38,
      "end": 72.9,
      "text": "they should not go among men openly in a body, and so be liable to attack from the hostile ills,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-015",
      "start": 72.9,
      "end": 78.06,
      "text": "but singly and unobserved, and are infrequent and unexpected intervals.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-016",
      "start": 79.12,
      "end": 84.36,
      "text": "Hence it is that the earth is full of ills, for they come and go as they please,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-017",
      "start": 85.14,
      "end": 90.44,
      "text": "and are never far away, while goods, alas, come one by one only,",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-018",
      "start": 91.24,
      "end": 95.28,
      "text": "and have to travel all the way from heaven, so that they are very seldom seen.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-019",
      "start": 96.48,
      "end": 99.36,
      "text": "End of the goods and the ills.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
